I agree with you that the True Gods would have intervened, but they aren't
who you think they are.

In a universe ruled by Stan Lee, a genocidal murderer would be executed (see
Dark Phoenix).

In a universe under Mort Weisinger, a genocidal murderer would either be
sentenced to eternal prison with no chance of parole (Jax-Ur) or turned to a
stone statue and then shattered by Jax-Ur (Black Zero).

In Julie Schwart's creation, a would-be genocidal murderer would be stopped
before succeeding.

In those days, heroes were heroes, and gods strode the earth.

But in a universe ruled by &quot;just a guy named Joe&quot;, civil war is forgiven and
genocide forgotten.

Jay Rudin
