The reason for Cap's actions is because Cap never has a plan. He makes
it up as he goes along, instead of planning for contingencies, because
when you are in the middle of a warzone, there is little time to plan
ahead. This is the difference between war veterans and actual
politicians. The reason Cap surrendered is because he knew that, in
the long run, his way of doing things was not going to work. There
needed to be a fundamental sea change in the mentality of the
leadership. Cap could have changed his mind and come to terms with
long term political thinking, but he is a soldier, not the general.
His job is to do and die. He did and died. Now it's time for a solid
realist to take over where airy fairy idealism has failed, regardless
